Episode 686 - Sean Parnell is a First Class Father, Combat Veteran and NYT Bestselling Author. He retired from military service as a highly decorated U.S. Army Captain, receiving 2 Bronze Stars (one for valor), and the Purple Heart. I sat down with Sean for this interview at CPAC in Washington DC.  Sean was endorsed by President Donald Trump in his US Senate bid in Pennsylvania but was forced to suspend his campaign due to a custody battle filled with false allegations by his ex wife.  Sean is now the host of Battleground Podcast where he talks about leadership & life with America’s most accomplished warriors, authors, media personalities, executives & political leaders.
In this Episode, Sean gives us an update on his kids and discusses the powerful and corrupt Family Court System in America.  He describes what he has learned so far from going through a painful and public custody battle and gives advice for dads on the onset of a divorce and custody struggle.  He talks about his new wife Melanie, and how they are managing with their blended family.  He offers some great advice for new or soon-to-be dads and more.

On Saturday Pennsyvania lost a great protector of our freedom and 2nd Amendment rights. His name was Kim Stolfer. He was the President of Firearms Owners Against Crime and a US Marine. If you didn’t know Kim, let me tell you something: he was tough as hell. He didn’t care what office you were running for, he just wanted to know your position on all things 2A. To Kim, protecting that right was everything. He made no qualms about it. He would also take time to educate you on that sacred right as well. 
It’s why I appreciated him so much. He never hesitated to school me or tell me what for. He was no BS. And in the political world that is a precious and rare thing. 

That’s him on the laptop computer to my right. Furiously taking notes on my positions. 😂

Please take a minute today and say a little prayer for him. He was one hell of an American and Pennsylvania will miss him for sure. I know I will. 

Semper Fi Kim. God speed! 🇺🇸

17 years ago today the men of #OutlawPlatoon took a stand. They refused to be daunted by impossible odds. Outnumbered 10:1, surrounded, and outgunned, my men stood shoulder to shoulder in the mountains of Afghanistan against an enemy hell-bent on our destruction. 

I, along with 50% of my platoon, was wounded. Never once did I witness a man quit, not even those critically wounded. I witnessed acts of heroism and selflessness that will stay with me forever. 

And in the end, we were victorious because of the quick thinking of our company commander. Just as we ran out of ammo, with the enemy all around, he, along with a platoon of Delta Reapers, showed up to rescue us. 

There isn't a day that goes by where I don't think about those men. Our deployment to Afghanistan was hell on Earth, but I consider myself blessed to have been there with them. The greatest irony of my life was that amidst all that death and destruction, what stood out to me the most was the love and brotherhood we had for one another. 

My Alive Day Pledge: I will always endeavor to live a life worthy of their sacrifice.
